# SOLAT Environment & Config Agent (8.2 rule)

When adding a Settings field or new env var in [engine/solat_engine/config.py](engine/solat_engine/config.py), ensure [.env.example](.env.example) is updated and non-obvious vars are documented in README or CONVENTIONS.

## Rules

- **config.py:** Use Field with default and description; use SecretStr for any credential; use env_prefix SOLAT_ (or alias for IG_*). Add validator if needed (e.g. log_level, data_dir).
- **.env.example:** Add every new env var used by config (or by app) with a comment; no real values.
- **Docs:** If the setting affects security, ports, or run behaviour, mention in [README.md](README.md) config table or [docs/CONVENTIONS.md](docs/CONVENTIONS.md).

Do not add secrets to .env.example; use placeholders like "your_api_key_here".
